article.headline: Purdue's early surge swamps Islanders
article.linkText: Boilermakers too strong for tournament host
article.story:
CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Tye Jackson had 17 points,
including four 3-pointers, as Purdue (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today; No. 15 AP) beat Texas A&M-Corpus
Christi 73-44 Friday night to win the Flint Hills Resources
Islander Classic.

Katie Gearlds and Erin Lawless added 12 points apiece for Purdue
(3-0), and Emily Heikes had a double-double with 10 points and 10
rebounds. Lindsay Wisdom-Hylton scored 10 points, had four assists
and blocked three shots for the Boilermakers.

Purdue led 5-4 with 17 minutes left in the first half before
going on an 18-3 run in the next 9 minutes to take a 23-7 lead.

Jackson hit two 3-pointers in the last 1:30 of the first half to
increase Purdue's lead to 36-16 at the break.

Purdue took advantage of 25 Texas A&M-Corpus Christi turnovers
to score 29 points.

Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (3-1) was led by Jackie Ododa and
Jillianne Duffey, who scored eight points each.

Purdue shot 51 percent from the field to just 26 percent by the
Islanders.
